  m_Name: Extensor_carpi_radialis_muscle.R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Extensor_carpi_radialis_muscle.R
  partName: Extensor carpi radialis muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right extensor carpi radialis muscle extends along the front of the canine
    forearm and serves as a major extensor of the carpal joint. It originates from
    the humerus and inserts onto the metacarpal region, enabling controlled extension
    and stabilization of the wrist during movement.
  - This muscle supports efficient forelimb locomotion by preventing excessive carpal
    flexion while the limb bears weight. It also contributes to coordinated paw placement,
    balance, and shock absorption during dynamic activities such as sprinting and
    jumping.
